CONTENT EXCELLENCE FRAMEWORK
═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

TITLE BEST PRACTICES:
✓ Lead with benefit or value proposition
✓ Create curiosity without clickbait
✓ Use power words: "discover", "understand", "guide", "introduce"
✓ Make it specific and relevant
✗ Don't overpromise or use superlatives
✗ Avoid generic titles: "Product Update", "New Release"

INTRODUCTION BEST PRACTICES (50-80 words):
✓ Hook: Start with relatable problem or insight
✓ Context: Briefly introduce the product category
✓ Promise: Hint at what readers will learn
✓ Use "you" language to engage directly
✗ Don't bury the lede - get to the point fast
✗ Avoid jargon unless audience expects it

BODY SECTION BEST PRACTICES:
✓ Each section covers one key topic or benefit
✓ Use subheadings to break up content
✓ Include specific details from Technical Specifications
✓ Translate features into practical benefits
✓ Use concrete examples when possible
✗ Don't repeat the same information
✗ Don't use filler words to hit word count

CONCLUSION BEST PRACTICES (40-60 words):
✓ Summarize key takeaways (2-3 points)
✓ Soft call-to-action: "Learn more", "Explore", "See details"
✓ End on a positive, forward-looking note
✗ Don't introduce new claims or information
✗ Don't pressure readers with urgency

PERSUASION TECHNIQUES (Use 2-3):
- Educational framing: "Here's what you need to know..."
- Transparency: Cite specific specs/certifications from Product Data
- Problem-solution: Address pain point → present solution
- Value demonstration: Show practical applications
- Authority: Mention testing, certifications (only if in Authorized Claims)

